vocabInfos.mediumDef:
A woman living at the time of the Patriarchs, first mentioned at Gen.41.45;
daughter of: Potiphera (H6319); married to Joseph (H3130);
mother of: Manasseh (H4519) and Ephraim (H0669)
§ Asenath = "belonging to the goddess Neith"
the wife of Joseph
vocabInfos._es_Definition: hija de Potifera; esposa de José
vocabInfos._zh_tw_Definition:
亞西納 这个陰性專有名詞在埃及文的意思是 "屬於 Neith 女神的"
約瑟的妻子
vocabInfos._zh_Definition:
亚西纳 这个阴性专有名词在埃及文的意思是 "属于 Neith 女神的"
约瑟的妻子
